{"key":"processedPost-10788027","value":{"id":10788027,"first":10787425,"last":10794752,"when":1249264283,"utime":"08/03/09 04:51 AM","content":"Interesting.&nbsp; I use the autoclavable filter patch bags from Unicorn Bag Company and have never had a single bag melt from contacting the sides of the PC.&nbsp; Obviously you have to elevate them off the bottom because that's where the heat is applied, but the sides shouldn't be hot enough to melt them.&nbsp; The important thing is to get spacers in place to hold the bags away from the edges so steam can completely surround them.&nbsp; If not, your substrate may not be fully sterilized.<br />RR","title":"Re: PC'er Vs. Oven"}}